Sitting down and listing all of your debts, the amounts, etc. We decided to the snowball method was best for us. Start by paying off the smallest of your debts and work up to the larger ones. What it does is make you feel a sense of accomplishment when you begin paying off the small ones. Then, take what you were throwing at one debt and add it to the next debt. Just eat the elephant one bite at a time :)
